                    <figDesc>Pen and ink, approx. 5.5 &#x00D7; 4.1 cm (image only). The editors of the <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="library_edition_note.html">Library Edition</ref> 
                        describe the image as a &#x201C;sketch of a street, with waggon and horses in the foreground&#x201D; 
                        (<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.html#JRWORKSLE">Ruskin, <hi rend="italic">Works</hi></ref>, 2:344 n. 2). 
                        The vignette is drawn in the manner of <ref type="note" subtype="biographical" target="prout_samuel_note.php">Samuel Prout (<date when="1783">1783</date>&#x2013;<date when="1852">1852</date>)</ref>, 
                        suggesting without specifically copying <title type="sketch" corresp="#PROUTGHENT">&#x201C;Ghent&#x201D;</title> 
                        in <title type="collected_sketches" corresp="#PROUTSKETCHES" rend="italic">Facsimiles</title>.
                    </figDesc>
